# The living roadmap's generated artifact and its two sources are byte-load-bearing.
#
# `npm run roadmap:check` compares roadmap.html byte-for-byte against a fresh
# render, and the Gateway reports the served bytes' SHA-256 as X-Roadmap-Sha256 so
# the published page can be verified against the committed artifact. scripts/roadmap.mjs
# writes all three with LF. With core.autocrlf=true — the default on Windows — a fresh
# clone would check them out as CRLF, which changes the bytes: roadmap:check then fails
# with a spurious "stale", the served SHA stops matching the artifact, and every render
# rewrites the files back to LF as permanent working-tree churn.
#
# Pin them to the bytes the generator writes. Comfy pins its evidence folder the same
# way, for the same reason (fieldlab/.gitattributes).
src/Game.Gateway/Community/roadmap.html -text
docs/roadmap/commit-notes.jsonl -text
docs/roadmap/valheim-volunteer-roadmap.json -text
